  "prompt": "If my ATM card is blocked for online transactions then how do i restart it?",
  "response": "If your ATM card is blocked for online transactions, you can typically restart it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Contact Your Bank**: The first step is to contact your bank\u2019s customer service. You can usually do this by calling their helpline or visiting a local branch. Explain your situation and ask them to unblock your card for online transactions.\n\n2. **Mobile Banking or Internet Banking**: If you have access to your bank's mobile or internet banking services, you might be able to manage your card settings there. Look for options related to card management, such as enabling or disabling online transactions, and make the necessary changes.\n\n3. **Visit the Branch**: If you prefer face-to-face assistance, visiting a local branch of your bank can be helpful. A bank representative can assist you in unblocking your card for online use.\n\n4. **Check for Alerts**: Sometimes, cards are blocked for security reasons. Make sure to check any messages or alerts from your bank that might explain why the card was blocked, as this might guide you on the necessary steps to unblock it.\n\n5. **ATM Reset Option**: Some banks provide an option to unblock or reset your card directly at an ATM. Follow the instructions on the ATM screen to manage card settings.\n\n6. **Follow Bank Protocols**: Banks have specific protocols for unblocking cards, and you may need to verify your identity or complete specific procedures as instructed by your bank.\n\nAlways confirm with your bank to ensure you\u2019re taking the correct steps specific to their processes.",
